The Boston University Terriers women's hockey team will represent Boston University in the [[2009â10 NCAA Division I women's ice hockey season]]. The Terriers are coached by Brian Durocher. Assisting Durocher are Katie Lachapelle, Allison Coomey and Todd Langlais.
==Offseason== *June 15: The Boston University women's ice hockey team will add a group of seven newcomers to its 2009-10 roster. The Terriers will welcome forwards Jill Cardella, Taylor Holze, Shannon Mahoney and Cristina Wiley, defensemen Britt Hergesheimer and Kathryn Miller and goaltender Alissa Fromkin, a talented group from across North America.<ref>http://www.goterriers.com/sports/w-hockey/spec-rel/061509aaa.html</ref> *June 24: Defenseman Amanda Shaw, who just completed a four-year career with the Boston University women's ice hockey team, has signed with a professional team in Switzerland and will also skate for Canada's national inline hockey team. Shaw will play for ZSC Lions in Zurich, a club in the Swiss women's professional ice hockey league.<ref>http://www.goterriers.com/sports/w-hockey/spec-rel/062409aaa.html</ref> *August 17: Sophomores Jenelle Kohanchuk and [[Tara Watchorn]] of the Boston University women's ice hockey team have been named to the 2009-10 Canadian National Women's Under-22 team, Hockey Canada announced this weekend. The squad will participate in a three-game series against the Canadian National Team that will take place from August 17â20 at Father David Bauer Olympic Arena in Calgary.<ref>http://www.goterriers.com/sports/w-hockey/spec-rel/081709aaa.html</ref>
==Regular season== *October 5: The Boston University womenâs hockey team was ranked No. 10 in the country. The USCHO.com officials revealed it in their first Top-10 Womenâs Hockey Poll of the season. BU accumulated 19 points.<ref>http://hurstathletics.com/news/2009/10/5/WHOCK_1005094806.aspx</ref> *On October 9, 2009, Boucher scored her first career goal and notched her first career multi-point game, as the Terriers defeated the Robert Morris Colonials by a 4-3 overtime tally.<ref>http://www.goterriers.com/sports/w-hockey/mtt/boucher_kasey00.html</ref> *November: Jill Cardella led all Hockey East rookies with nine points and six goals in league play. The freshman had a five-game point streak from Nov. 2 to Nov. 14, and had the game-winning goal in a 4-0 shutout of Vermont on Nov. 11, and scored the most goals (6) of any player in the month of November in league action. *February 17: Melissa Anderson of Boston University is among one of forty five nominees for the [[Patty Kazmaier Memorial Award]].<ref>http://www.usahockey.com/patty_kazmaier/default.aspx?NAV=AF&id=280824&DetailedNews=yes</ref>
